### ======================================================================
### Vezeeta Backend — HTTP request file
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### Works with VS Code "REST Client", JetBrains HTTP Client, etc.
### Pairs with the Swagger UI at /api/docs.
###
### Variables are defined per-request when needed; better-auth session
### cookies are stored in `cookies.vezeta.session_token` by the REST
### Client jar. Edit the variables below before sending.
### ======================================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@email = jane.patient@example.com
@password = ChangeMe123!
@doctorProfileId = replace-me-with-doctor-profile-id
@userId = replace-me-with-user-id

### 1) Health probe (public) ---------------------------------------------

# @name health
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health
Accept: application/json

### 2) Better Auth — sign up a patient -----------------------------------
# Returns Set-Cookie: vezeta.session_token=... (also stores in jar).

# @name signUpPatient
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-up/email
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: {{baseUrl}}

{
  "name": "Jane Patient",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "role": "patient"
}

### 3) Better Auth — sign in (stores cookie for next calls) -------------

# @name signIn
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-in/email
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: {{baseUrl}}

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 4) Get the current session user ---------------------------------------

# @name me
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/me
Accept: application/json

### 5) Doctor-only test route (requires role=doctor + APPROVED profile) -

# @name doctorTest
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/doctors/test-route
Accept: application/json

### 6) Better Auth — sign out --------------------------------------------

# @name signOut
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-out
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: {{baseUrl}}

### 7) Admin — list doctors (requires role=admin) ------------------------

# @name listDoctors
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/doctors?status=PENDING
Accept: application/json

### 8) Admin — list doctors with no status filter ------------------------

# @name listAllDoctors
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/doctors
Accept: application/json

### 9) Admin — approve a doctor ------------------------------------------

# @name approveDoctor
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/doctors/{{doctorProfileId}}/approve
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "Verified medical license via email."
}

### 10) Admin — reject a doctor ------------------------------------------

# @name rejectDoctor
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/doctors/{{doctorProfileId}}/reject
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "License number could not be verified."
}

### 11) Admin — suspend a doctor -----------------------------------------

# @name suspendDoctor
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/doctors/{{doctorProfileId}}/suspend
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "Pending review for policy violation."
}

### 12) Admin — deactivate a user ----------------------------------------

# @name deactivateUser
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{userId}}/deactivate
Accept: application/json

### 13) Admin — ping (public) --------------------------------------------

# @name adminPing
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/ping
Accept: application/json

### 14) Negative — call /api/me without a session ------------------------
# Expect 401.

# @name meUnauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/me
Accept: application/json

### 15) Negative — call admin route as a non-admin ----------------------
# Sign in as the patient first (see #3), then send.

# @name adminForbidden
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/doctors
Accept: application/json
